Defendant Demetrice L Ambers in court, in custody, with Attorney Joseph Smith.   Mary C. Brejcha appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State files an amended information.  Defendant enters a no contest plea to Count #1 on amended information.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1 on amended information.  State gives sentencing recommendation.  Attorney Smith makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

5  YEARS IMPRISONMENT 
  -  3 YEARS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  2 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISON 

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEARS

CONDITIONS OF PROBATON:  
____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
____Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
____No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs/drug paraphernalia 
____No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
____Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
____No contact with: victims/businesses listed in criminal complaint or with co-actor
____DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done 

RESTITUTION:  $750.00 (Joint and several with Co-actor) (to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines)

COSTS:  $278.00 & $250.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid as a condition of probation)

CONDITION TIME:  7 MONTHS (127 days credit) - Non-working hours with standard release conditions to commence forthwith (Defendant already in custody).

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program. 

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
